First video, I have a hard time believing. I can understand that the guy 
holding the camera didn't want to go in the bathroom, but it can easily be 
debunked with how he was just standing there. He could've given the other 
guy the camera, if all he was going to do was peek in the bathroom. I'm not 
saying that wasn't paranormal shit, because it might've been. The fact is, 
we don't know if they were playing something, and a guy was hiding in 
there. TV, where the camera guy's side was is where the TV is. Again, not 
saying it's not paranormal shit. But I'm having a very hard time believing 
it.
Second video, the stain. The floor is reflective, and might have been 
reflecting the wall beside it. The "stain" also doesn't cover the 
decoration on the floor. Otherwise, it's a hotel. Lot's of stains are 
around hotels. Elisa wasn't even on that floor, if you pay attention to the 
colors of the walls. This wall is orange. The wall on the floor Elisa was 
on is either dark blue or purple. The "strange mist". If you look at the 
quality around the rest of the elevator, it matches the quality where this 
was. The color is off, yes. But it could also just be the quality of the 
security camera. The fact that the mist stays there, proves my point. I 
don't see the strange face, in all honesty. The elevator? There's another 
video of someone going through the hotel to test the Elisa Lam case, and if 
you push the hold button, it does that same thing. We don't know if she did 
push this button, because her head covers it while she's pushing all the 
buttons. I don't see this strange reflection, either. If anything, it's 
Elisa. You also have this video playing backwards. Her face? That's her 
hand. Shadow being?? Really. That's been there the entire video. The time 
being edited is true. If you don't believe this, this video should clear 
things up: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1YO4QbaNDjI And everyone 
questioning the "strange foot", that's her own foot. If you watch the way 
her feet are while she's walking away, this foot matches the way Elisa 
moves her feet, and the timing. Again, I'm not saying the death of Elisa 
Lam is not paranormal, but it might not be. It could be exactly what the 
authorities say, an accident. It could have been a murder. The fact is, we 
don't know. Unless you watched it happen or you killed her, there is no 
possibility that we know exactly what happened.
Please view things skeptically while you're watching things, because most 
of this is very easily debunked.﻿
